# React Native Conventions

- Fetch data through a dedicated API/service layer, not inline in components.
- Always handle loading and error states explicitly.
- Keep the UI responsive after updates (optimistic UI or fast local state sync).
- Use functional components and hooks; keep components small and composable.
- Separate presentation from data-fetching logic.
- Consistent naming and clear file organization.
